Scenario: Secure Access Management for a Small Company
Objective

Implement secure access control using Azure RBAC by creating:

2 Users
2 Groups
Assign users to groups
Provide different access permissions.
Resources
Users
Employee1
Username: employee1@yourtenant.onmicrosoft.com
GuestUser
Invite an external guest user or create:
guestuser@yourtenant.onmicrosoft.com
Groups
Group 1: Developers

Purpose:

Manage Virtual Machines.
Group 2: StorageTeam

Purpose:

Manage Storage Accounts.
Implementation Steps
Step 1: Create Users

Azure Portal →
Azure Active Directory →
Users →
New User

Create:

Employee1
GuestUser
Step 2: Create Groups

Azure Active Directory →
Groups →
New Group

Create:

Developers
StorageTeam
Step 3: Add Users to Groups
Group	Member
Developers	Employee1
StorageTeam	GuestUser
Step 4: Create Resources

Create:

1 Virtual Machine
1 Storage Account
Step 5: Assign RBAC Roles
Group	Resource	Role
Developers	Virtual Machine	Virtual Machine Contributor
StorageTeam	Storage Account	Storage Blob Data Contributor
Testing
Employee1

✅ Can manage VM.

❌ Cannot manage Storage Account.

GuestUser

✅ Can upload/download blobs.

❌ Cannot manage VM.

Architecture
                    Azure Subscription
                           |
                  -------------------
                  |                 |
            Developers       StorageTeam
                  |                 |
           Employee1         GuestUser
                  |                 |
          VM Contributor    Blob Contributor
                  |                 |
          Virtual Machine   Storage Account
Expected Output

✅ Two users created.

✅ Two groups created.

✅ Users added to respective groups.

✅ RBAC roles assigned.

✅ Resource access restricted according to assigned roles
